1
00:00:01,979 --> 00:00:05,023
On our way home from school, we ran into

2
00:00:05,107 --> 00:00:07,985
Yumi Miyamoto and Naeko Miike in their mini-patrol car.

3
00:00:08,735 --> 00:00:12,739
Just then, Naeko received a call about an incident.

4
00:00:13,323 --> 00:00:15,242
When we rushed to the scene,

5
00:00:15,325 --> 00:00:18,704
there was a body hanging from a chandelier.

6
00:00:19,705 --> 00:00:24,251
There was what looked like a suicide note at her feet,
so we thought it was a suicide, but...

7
00:00:25,752 --> 00:00:27,671
I see. Hmm?

8
00:00:29,339 --> 00:00:34,219
So that's what you meant by "the one move you prepared"?

9
00:00:35,053 --> 00:00:37,973
"The one move you prepared."

10
00:00:38,056 --> 00:00:40,058
That's... if I remember correctly...

11
00:00:40,434 --> 00:00:46,440
♪~♪

12
00:00:53,447 --> 00:00:56,158
The blackness of shadows, the density of darkness—
the light of reasoning cuts right through them.

13
00:00:56,825 --> 00:01:00,537
The suspect is Yumi Miyamoto's ex-boyfriend?
A single move of deduction at the clogged scene.

14
00:01:01,079 --> 00:01:02,539
See through the one and only truth.

15
00:01:02,623 --> 00:01:04,499
Looks like a kid, but has the mind of an adult.

16
00:01:04,583 --> 00:01:07,169
His name is Detective Conan!

17
00:02:31,756 --> 00:02:37,762
♪~♪

18
00:02:39,470 --> 00:02:44,570
"The Neighbor at the Site is an Ex-Boyfriend (Part 2)"

19
00:02:45,019 --> 00:02:46,271
(Door opens) Chief Megure!

20
00:02:46,354 --> 00:02:47,480
Hmm?

21
00:02:47,564 --> 00:02:49,733
We have an eyewitness account of a suspicious person.

22
00:02:49,816 --> 00:02:51,609
What? Hmm?

23
00:02:52,026 --> 00:02:54,779
According to the concierge in the first floor lobby,

24
00:02:54,863 --> 00:02:57,907
a suspicious person with their face hidden by a hat, mask, and glasses

25
00:02:57,991 --> 00:03:00,118
entered and left the condo.

26
00:03:00,201 --> 00:03:02,162
Wow! Chi... Chiba-kun.

27
00:03:02,579 --> 00:03:04,164
When was that?

28
00:03:04,247 --> 00:03:07,417
Apparently it was after the master and housekeeper left.

29
00:03:07,834 --> 00:03:10,545
Why didn't the concierge stop him?

30
00:03:10,628 --> 00:03:14,591
He used a key to enter normally, so he was thought to be a resident.

31
00:03:14,674 --> 00:03:17,218
Also, he said the son came by too.

32
00:03:17,302 --> 00:03:18,636
The son?

33
00:03:18,720 --> 00:03:19,763
Hmm? Yes.

34
00:03:20,263 --> 00:03:22,557
He said it was before the master and housekeeper returned,

35
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:23,892
but

36
00:03:23,975 --> 00:03:26,811
whether the suspicious person left before or after that,

37
00:03:26,895 --> 00:03:28,480
he couldn't remember.

38
00:03:28,563 --> 00:03:29,981
Huh? Huh?

39
00:03:30,523 --> 00:03:34,360
Could you be... (Heartbeat)

40
00:03:34,652 --> 00:03:37,822
Sakurako-chan? One year below me? Huh?

41
00:03:37,906 --> 00:03:41,159
Ah, Chiba-chi. Long time no see.

42
00:03:41,242 --> 00:03:44,662
What, so the housekeeper is Sakurako-chan?

43
00:03:45,330 --> 00:03:49,209
Why won't you remember me?

44
00:03:49,292 --> 00:03:52,420
Ah, come to think of it, you might not remember,

45
00:03:52,504 --> 00:03:55,215
but I was often with you... (Doorbell)

46
00:03:55,381 --> 00:03:57,592
Chiba-kun, go check that.

47
00:03:57,675 --> 00:03:59,177
Ah, yes.

48
00:03:59,260 --> 00:04:01,429
Hey, what's with this kid?

49
00:04:01,513 --> 00:04:03,181
Let go... Huh?

50
00:04:03,264 --> 00:04:07,685
Like I'd let go! You... ugh...

51
00:04:07,769 --> 00:04:09,813
Wh... what are you kids doing?

52
00:04:09,896 --> 00:04:13,149
What do you mean? We caught a suspicious guy!

53
00:04:13,233 --> 00:04:16,236
It's not like I'm suspicious or anything...

54
00:04:16,319 --> 00:04:19,656
You were peeking inside through the peephole, weren't you?

55
00:04:19,906 --> 00:04:21,741
I was just joking around.

56
00:04:21,825 --> 00:04:24,828
I thought it'd be funny if someone peeked back and got scared.

57
00:04:24,911 --> 00:04:28,998
Besides, even if you peek from outside, you can't see inside.

58
00:04:29,290 --> 00:04:31,960
But your hair is weird too.

59
00:04:32,043 --> 00:04:33,378
Ugh... th-this is...

60
00:04:34,045 --> 00:04:37,048
I just let my dyed hair grow out and it ended up like this.

61
00:04:37,131 --> 00:04:38,925
That's what you say, but

62
00:04:39,008 --> 00:04:41,177
you actually came back because you were worried, didn't you?

63
00:04:41,761 --> 00:04:44,556
They say the culprit returns to the scene.

64
00:04:44,639 --> 00:04:49,310
C-culprit? What are you talking about?

65
00:04:49,394 --> 00:04:51,980
Hey, is it true you were peeking?

66
00:04:52,063 --> 00:04:55,942
Ah... yes. This man rang the doorbell suddenly, and then

67
00:04:56,234 --> 00:04:58,194
That voice... Yasue?

68
00:04:58,278 --> 00:05:00,613
Ah, Dad. Hmm?

69
00:05:01,698 --> 00:05:05,034
...So this guy is the son.

70
00:05:06,077 --> 00:05:07,120
What's wrong?

71
00:05:07,203 --> 00:05:09,414
Weren't you at driving school?

72
00:05:09,497 --> 00:05:13,418
I skipped. I wanted to show you the car catalog as soon as possible.

73
00:05:13,501 --> 00:05:17,505
Car, nothing. Worry about that after you find a job.

74
00:05:17,589 --> 00:05:21,467
What's your problem? You agreed to me getting a license.

75
00:05:21,801 --> 00:05:24,929
With that pudding-head of yours, there's no way you'll pass.

76
00:05:25,221 --> 00:05:28,433
Hey, Dad, why are you so irritated?

77
00:05:28,892 --> 00:05:31,519
There are cops here. Did something happen?

78
00:05:31,603 --> 00:05:33,938
Ah, well...

79
00:05:34,439 --> 00:05:36,941
Huh? Mom committed suicide?

80
00:05:37,191 --> 00:05:39,444
No way... why?

81
00:05:39,527 --> 00:05:42,822
The possibility that she was murdered still remains.

82
00:05:42,906 --> 00:05:45,074
M-murdered?

83
00:05:45,158 --> 00:05:49,162
Come to think of it, I heard you came here once today.

84
00:05:49,537 --> 00:05:53,082
Ah... yes. To show him this catalog.

85
00:05:53,166 --> 00:05:56,210
But when I rang the doorbell, no one answered,

86
00:05:56,294 --> 00:05:58,212
so I thought they went out shopping,

87
00:05:58,296 --> 00:06:01,633
wandered around for a while, and came back.

88
00:06:02,425 --> 00:06:05,470
I see. Can anyone prove that?

89
00:06:05,845 --> 00:06:07,722
H-hey, Inspector.

90
00:06:07,805 --> 00:06:09,766
You're not suspecting me, are you?

91
00:06:09,849 --> 00:06:10,850
(Cell phone vibrates) Huh?

92
00:06:10,934 --> 00:06:12,602
Someone's phone is ringing.

93
00:06:12,977 --> 00:06:15,313
Huh? (Cell phone vibrates)

94
00:06:18,149 --> 00:06:21,653
Ah, sorry. That was my phone.

95
00:06:21,736 --> 00:06:22,779
...Geez.

96
00:06:23,071 --> 00:06:26,908
So all three of you have the same phone?

97
00:06:26,991 --> 00:06:30,453
Ah, yeah. This model is popular.

98
00:06:30,536 --> 00:06:33,706
The covers are different colors, so we don't mix them up.

99
00:06:33,957 --> 00:06:35,249
Hmm.

100
00:06:35,333 --> 00:06:39,379
Speaking of phones, before you found the wife's phone,

101
00:06:39,462 --> 00:06:42,131
you heard the bedroom door close,

102
00:06:42,215 --> 00:06:43,883
didn't you, Sakurako-san?

103
00:06:43,967 --> 00:06:44,968
Uh... yes.

104
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:49,138
How did you know that sound came from the bedroom?

105
00:06:49,222 --> 00:06:51,474
You can't see it from the entrance.

106
00:06:51,557 --> 00:06:54,310
All the other doors were slightly open.

107
00:06:54,769 --> 00:06:57,855
I thought they were closed before we went shopping.

108
00:06:57,939 --> 00:07:01,150
Then was the bedroom window slightly open too?

109
00:07:01,234 --> 00:07:03,569
Huh? How do you know that?

110
00:07:03,653 --> 00:07:06,781
Were you with her the whole time during shopping?

111
00:07:06,864 --> 00:07:10,868
No, I was in the smoking area until the shopping was done...

112
00:07:10,952 --> 00:07:14,205
Then the master has no alibi either.

113
00:07:14,497 --> 00:07:16,833
Haneda-san, were you at home the whole time?

114
00:07:16,916 --> 00:07:18,835
No, I went out.

115
00:07:18,918 --> 00:07:21,713
Right after I got back, the police officer rang the doorbell.

116
00:07:21,796 --> 00:07:24,340
Where did you go and what did you do?

117
00:07:24,424 --> 00:07:25,675
Well...

118
00:07:25,758 --> 00:07:28,678
Come on, just say it already.

119
00:07:30,179 --> 00:07:31,723
I can't say that.

120
00:07:31,931 --> 00:07:33,558
Huh? Hmm?

121
00:07:33,641 --> 00:07:34,726
Whoa...

122
00:07:35,059 --> 00:07:37,186
What are you saying, Chuukichi?

123
00:07:37,270 --> 00:07:40,356
You're being suspected of murder, you know.

124
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:44,944
Come on, say it. Otherwise you'll be treated like the culprit.

125
00:07:45,028 --> 00:07:46,738
It's okay, Yumi-tan.

126
00:07:47,530 --> 00:07:49,240
This case has already

127
00:07:49,574 --> 00:07:51,492
been solved.

128
00:08:02,099 --> 00:08:03,475
Listen up, you guys.

129
00:08:03,559 --> 00:08:05,978
It's definitely somewhere in this neighborhood.

130
00:08:06,228 --> 00:08:08,397
When you find it, show the photo I emailed you

131
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:12,192
to someone nearby to confirm.

132
00:08:12,276 --> 00:08:14,153
Okay. Got it.

133
00:08:14,236 --> 00:08:16,697
Yeah! Yeah, yeah.

134
00:08:17,072 --> 00:08:20,659
Chief Megure, the handwriting analysis results are in.

135
00:08:20,743 --> 00:08:22,077
Oh, is that so?

136
00:08:22,369 --> 00:08:24,705
The handwriting is quite distorted,

137
00:08:24,788 --> 00:08:28,916
but there's no doubt that the note was written by Itami Chiyoko-san herself.

138
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,461
What?

139
00:08:30,836 --> 00:08:34,173
So there's no chance she was forced to write it by the culprit?

140
00:08:34,256 --> 00:08:36,508
No. With it that distorted,

141
00:08:36,592 --> 00:08:38,969
the culprit would have made her rewrite it.

142
00:08:39,636 --> 00:08:42,681
Ah, also, the supermarket's security camera

143
00:08:42,765 --> 00:08:45,517
showed the housekeeper frequently,

144
00:08:45,601 --> 00:08:48,479
so her alibi is confirmed.

145
00:08:48,562 --> 00:08:52,941
The master, Naginobu-san, who went shopping with her,

146
00:08:53,025 --> 00:08:54,693
didn't appear on camera.

147
00:08:54,777 --> 00:08:57,154
That's because I was in the smoking area...

148
00:08:57,237 --> 00:09:00,157
So the suspects are the master,

149
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:03,994
the son Yasue-san, and me.

150
00:09:04,077 --> 00:09:09,708
The son came once, rang the doorbell, got no answer,
killed some time, then came back.

151
00:09:09,792 --> 00:09:11,710
I was out at the time of the crime,

152
00:09:11,794 --> 00:09:15,839
but I won't say where I went.

153
00:09:16,548 --> 00:09:20,135
Won't say? You're one to talk.

154
00:09:20,219 --> 00:09:24,723
Th-that's why I said I'll tell you where I went later.

155
00:09:24,807 --> 00:09:27,643
What, you can't say it in front of me?

156
00:09:27,893 --> 00:09:31,271
It's a woman. You were meeting some woman, weren't you?

157
00:09:31,355 --> 00:09:32,648
That's not true.

158
00:09:33,023 --> 00:09:36,318
I told you, you're the only one for me, Yumi-tan.

159
00:09:36,401 --> 00:09:38,070
How troublesome.

160
00:09:38,612 --> 00:09:42,866
Inspector, just say this guy is the culprit and cuff him already.

161
00:09:42,950 --> 00:09:45,786
B-but, Yumi-kun.

162
00:09:46,578 --> 00:09:49,373
Ah... there are some unclear points, but

163
00:09:49,456 --> 00:09:50,874
when the master and housekeeper

164
00:09:50,958 --> 00:09:53,794
returned from shopping and entered the front door,

165
00:09:53,877 --> 00:09:57,047
they heard the bedroom door close,

166
00:09:57,130 --> 00:10:01,218
and inside the bedroom, the wife had hanged herself.

167
00:10:01,510 --> 00:10:05,973
And if the note at her feet was written by the wife herself,

168
00:10:06,056 --> 00:10:07,933
then it can only be a suicide...

169
00:10:08,016 --> 00:10:10,269
"The one move you prepared." Hmm?

170
00:10:10,727 --> 00:10:12,938
That's what that note was all about, right?

171
00:10:13,021 --> 00:10:14,731
Haneda-san. Huh?

172
00:10:14,815 --> 00:10:17,734
Come to think of it, Chuukichi, you said something like that.

173
00:10:18,151 --> 00:10:20,195
What was that? What did you mean?

174
00:10:20,279 --> 00:10:24,074
W-well... did I say that?

175
00:10:25,075 --> 00:10:27,286
It's when you anticipate a certain situation

176
00:10:27,369 --> 00:10:31,999
and then, when that situation arrives, you make a brilliant move.

177
00:10:32,082 --> 00:10:36,128
I read online that it's called "the one move you prepared."

178
00:10:36,545 --> 00:10:38,797
It's apparently a shogi term.

179
00:10:38,881 --> 00:10:43,427
Shogi term? Why would Chuukichi know something like that?

180
00:10:43,886 --> 00:10:47,431
More importantly, why is that note "the one move you prepared"?

181
00:10:47,723 --> 00:10:51,268
Didn't you think the contents of that note were strange?

182
00:10:51,351 --> 00:10:54,271
Let's see, it said...

183
00:10:54,354 --> 00:10:58,984
"I'm sorry for injuring you. I pray for your speedy recovery."

184
00:10:59,067 --> 00:11:02,905
"Yasue-san, do your best on your exam. I know you'll pass."

185
00:11:02,988 --> 00:11:07,492
"For Ichiko-chan's Shichi-Go-San, please dress her in my furisode."

186
00:11:07,576 --> 00:11:12,205
"Please forgive me for leaving you so suddenly. Itami Chiyoko."

187
00:11:12,289 --> 00:11:13,874
What about this is...

188
00:11:13,957 --> 00:11:15,709
The part about the exam.

189
00:11:15,792 --> 00:11:17,502
Hmm?

190
00:11:17,836 --> 00:11:22,215
The exam Yasue-san is taking is the written test for a driver's license.

191
00:11:22,507 --> 00:11:25,928
It's not the kind of exam you need to pray so hard for.

192
00:11:26,011 --> 00:11:29,014
M-my wife was a worrier.

193
00:11:29,097 --> 00:11:33,143
In fact, she was quite worried about our son, who hasn't found a job

194
00:11:33,435 --> 00:11:35,604
even though he's graduating from university.

195
00:11:35,687 --> 00:11:39,149
Yes. Yasue-san is currently a university senior.

196
00:11:39,733 --> 00:11:41,318
If that note was written four years ago

197
00:11:41,401 --> 00:11:45,530
to her son who was preparing for his university entrance exams,

198
00:11:45,614 --> 00:11:48,200
wouldn't that make sense?

199
00:11:48,450 --> 00:11:51,995
Th-that's true, but four years ago...

200
00:11:52,079 --> 00:11:53,288
Four years ago,

201
00:11:53,372 --> 00:11:57,042
her niece Ichiko, who is now seven, would have been three,

202
00:11:57,125 --> 00:11:59,169
so Shichi-Go-San. Yes.

203
00:11:59,419 --> 00:12:04,007
I saw that photo recently. The lady showed it to me.

204
00:12:04,091 --> 00:12:06,927
Pointing to a little girl in a furisode, she said,

205
00:12:07,010 --> 00:12:11,223
"You can't tell this kimono is 40 years old, can you?"

206
00:12:11,598 --> 00:12:14,977
Then that note really was from four years ago...

207
00:12:15,060 --> 00:12:18,605
That's ridiculous. You saw this bruise on my eye, didn't you?

208
00:12:18,897 --> 00:12:23,110
It's from an ashtray my wife threw last night.

209
00:12:23,193 --> 00:12:24,945
If that injury is mentioned in the note...

210
00:12:25,028 --> 00:12:26,363
Speaking of injuries,

211
00:12:26,446 --> 00:12:29,783
I believe you also said you broke your leg before.

212
00:12:29,866 --> 00:12:31,785
Ah... yes.

213
00:12:32,327 --> 00:12:35,664
Mom was a beginner skier and crashed into Dad.

214
00:12:35,747 --> 00:12:39,001
Because of that, she had to fly alone

215
00:12:39,084 --> 00:12:41,628
to the annual New Year's party in the countryside,

216
00:12:41,712 --> 00:12:45,799
and she often told me how she nearly lost her life.

217
00:12:45,882 --> 00:12:48,218
So that was also four years ago.

218
00:12:48,301 --> 00:12:51,138
If that plane nearly crashed,

219
00:12:51,763 --> 00:12:54,516
it wouldn't be strange for her to write a suicide note on board,

220
00:12:54,599 --> 00:12:57,811
addressed to her family.

221
00:12:58,103 --> 00:13:02,315
I see. That's why the handwriting was shaky.

222
00:13:02,399 --> 00:13:05,193
Because she wrote it on a plane that was shaking.

223
00:13:05,277 --> 00:13:08,655
I see. And the reason she wrote her full name

224
00:13:08,739 --> 00:13:13,326
was to make it clear whose note it was when found at the crash site.

225
00:13:14,036 --> 00:13:15,620
If the culprit got hold of that note

226
00:13:15,704 --> 00:13:19,166
and used it in this murder four years later,

227
00:13:19,249 --> 00:13:22,335
then it would truly be "the one move he prepared."

228
00:13:22,586 --> 00:13:25,380
But when the master and housekeeper returned,

229
00:13:25,464 --> 00:13:28,467
the bedroom door closing is still a mystery.

230
00:13:28,550 --> 00:13:30,719
Ah. M-maybe

231
00:13:31,344 --> 00:13:35,140
the culprit was still hiding in the bedroom at that time?

232
00:13:35,432 --> 00:13:37,476
I don't think that's possible.

233
00:13:37,559 --> 00:13:40,771
When we returned, I locked the front door.

234
00:13:40,854 --> 00:13:44,691
And when Conan-kun first came, the lock was still on.

235
00:13:45,108 --> 00:13:47,694
So why did the door...

236
00:13:47,778 --> 00:13:50,447
It wouldn't close by itself.

237
00:13:50,530 --> 00:13:51,531
Ah.

238
00:13:51,615 --> 00:13:54,826
Hey, who's that? So rough.

239
00:13:54,910 --> 00:13:57,370
Could it be Chiba-kun? Huh?

240
00:13:58,038 --> 00:13:59,498
Hey, Conan-kun.

241
00:13:59,998 --> 00:14:02,876
Did you just close this door, Conan-kun?

242
00:14:02,959 --> 00:14:05,754
What do you mean? I opened the front door

243
00:14:05,837 --> 00:14:08,924
to check if my friends had come back.

244
00:14:09,424 --> 00:14:12,177
But I did open the bedroom window a little.

245
00:14:12,260 --> 00:14:14,429
The heating was too strong, and it was hot.

246
00:14:14,971 --> 00:14:18,892
The window was slightly open when we found the lady too.

247
00:14:18,975 --> 00:14:20,268
Is that true?

248
00:14:20,352 --> 00:14:21,436
Ah, yes.

249
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:24,022
The master said it would be sad for her to be cold,

250
00:14:24,106 --> 00:14:26,566
so he closed it immediately.

251
00:14:26,650 --> 00:14:28,360
That's it. Huh?

252
00:14:28,777 --> 00:14:30,904
When the front door was opened,

253
00:14:30,987 --> 00:14:34,658
the warm air inside rushed out the window,

254
00:14:34,741 --> 00:14:37,160
and the bedroom door closed.

255
00:14:37,661 --> 00:14:39,412
So the culprit left the bedroom window and door open

256
00:14:39,496 --> 00:14:42,624
so that would happen.

257
00:14:42,707 --> 00:14:45,752
But if that was the case, when the culprit tried to escape

258
00:14:45,836 --> 00:14:48,672
and opened the front door, it would have closed then too.

259
00:14:49,214 --> 00:14:50,674
That's true...

260
00:14:50,757 --> 00:14:53,343
Come to think of it, the wife's phone

261
00:14:53,426 --> 00:14:55,887
was on the floor in front of the bedroom door.

262
00:14:55,971 --> 00:14:58,181
Ah, yes. Then what if

263
00:14:58,598 --> 00:15:02,727
you wedged the phone in the door gap to keep it open?

264
00:15:04,062 --> 00:15:05,689
Like this.

265
00:15:06,064 --> 00:15:09,192
But then it would just stay open.

266
00:15:09,276 --> 00:15:10,694
I guess it's impossible.

267
00:15:11,319 --> 00:15:15,448
If the phone had legs and could move like a living thing,

268
00:15:15,532 --> 00:15:17,242
then maybe...

269
00:15:17,325 --> 00:15:19,786
Th-that's right! The phone's vibration.

270
00:15:19,870 --> 00:15:22,998
The culprit wedged the phone in the door, left the room,

271
00:15:23,081 --> 00:15:25,125
called the phone from outside,

272
00:15:25,208 --> 00:15:28,253
and the vibration made it fall and dislodge.

273
00:15:29,045 --> 00:15:32,425
But the wife's phone found on the floor

274
00:15:32,507 --> 00:15:34,134
had no call history.

275
00:15:34,426 --> 00:15:36,553
Maybe that's not the wife's phone.

276
00:15:36,636 --> 00:15:38,305
Huh? Hmm?

277
00:15:38,722 --> 00:15:40,223
Because all three of them

278
00:15:40,307 --> 00:15:43,059
have the same phone, just with different colored covers.

279
00:15:43,643 --> 00:15:46,897
It wouldn't be strange if someone took the wife's phone by mistake,

280
00:15:46,980 --> 00:15:48,440
thinking it was their own.

281
00:15:48,523 --> 00:15:52,277
I see. If you remove the wife's phone cover

282
00:15:52,360 --> 00:15:56,948
and put it on your own phone, you can pretend it's the wife's.

283
00:15:57,365 --> 00:16:00,202
Use that phone in the trick,

284
00:16:00,285 --> 00:16:04,289
then put the cover back before handing it over to the police,

285
00:16:04,372 --> 00:16:09,002
and it would seem the wife's phone wasn't used in the crime.

286
00:16:09,336 --> 00:16:11,963
And the only person who could have done that

287
00:16:12,422 --> 00:16:16,176
is the one who had the wife's phone until handing it over to us—

288
00:16:16,509 --> 00:16:19,930
the master, Naginobu-san. It can only be you.

289
00:16:22,098 --> 00:16:23,642
What you likely did was:

290
00:16:23,725 --> 00:16:26,978
You went home while the housekeeper was shopping,

291
00:16:27,062 --> 00:16:30,148
strangled your wife, hung her from the ceiling,

292
00:16:30,232 --> 00:16:34,694
placed the four-year-old suicide note at her feet, opened the bedroom window,

293
00:16:34,778 --> 00:16:38,198
wedged the phone in the door, and left.

294
00:16:38,698 --> 00:16:41,618
Then you called that phone from outside,

295
00:16:41,701 --> 00:16:44,704
the vibration dislodged the phone from the door,

296
00:16:44,788 --> 00:16:47,916
you met up with the housekeeper and returned home again,

297
00:16:47,999 --> 00:16:52,212
and made it look like your wife had committed suicide.

298
00:16:52,754 --> 00:16:56,841
The reason you didn't go into the bedroom immediately after returning

299
00:16:56,925 --> 00:16:58,426
was to hide the fact that

300
00:16:58,510 --> 00:17:01,596
some time had passed since the body was hung.

301
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:05,600
Then the suspicious person the concierge saw...

302
00:17:05,684 --> 00:17:07,102
was you.

303
00:17:07,602 --> 00:17:11,106
You probably had a change of clothes ready in the supermarket bathroom.

304
00:17:11,523 --> 00:17:15,360
Well, we'll know once we check your phone.

305
00:17:15,443 --> 00:17:19,489
C-come to think of it, while I was in the supermarket smoking area, I got a call...

306
00:17:19,572 --> 00:17:21,658
From who? Ah, th-that was...

307
00:17:21,741 --> 00:17:23,785
it seemed to be a wrong number.

308
00:17:23,868 --> 00:17:24,911
(Cell phone vibrates) Hmm...

309
00:17:26,121 --> 00:17:28,039
We found a public phone!

310
00:17:28,331 --> 00:17:30,709
It's in front of the convenience store nearby.

311
00:17:31,042 --> 00:17:33,420
When we showed the store manager a photo of the master,

312
00:17:33,503 --> 00:17:36,256
he testified that he was "sneakily using the phone."

313
00:17:36,589 --> 00:17:40,593
Well, not many people use public phones these days,

314
00:17:40,802 --> 00:17:43,179
so there might still be fingerprints.

315
00:17:43,513 --> 00:17:44,597
So there.

316
00:17:44,681 --> 00:17:46,599
Ah... ah...

317
00:17:47,559 --> 00:17:49,853
B-but is it true, Dad?

318
00:17:50,395 --> 00:17:52,564
Did Dad really kill Mom?

319
00:17:53,356 --> 00:17:56,651
I thought my luck had finally turned around.

320
00:17:57,805 --> 00:17:57,902
Huh?

321
00:17:58,236 --> 00:18:01,740
To be honest, I was hesitant about carrying out this murder plan.

322
00:18:01,823 --> 00:18:03,283
Until last night.

323
00:18:03,783 --> 00:18:05,410
Hey, Chiyoko.

324
00:18:06,202 --> 00:18:07,287
I told you to quit stocks.

325
00:18:07,954 --> 00:18:10,290
But you know, even though you said no,

326
00:18:10,373 --> 00:18:15,168
don't you want to buy a car for Yasue?

327
00:18:15,251 --> 00:18:19,670
What are you saying? Our debt is already huge.

328
00:18:19,962 --> 00:18:21,674
I've figured it out!

329
00:18:21,766 --> 00:18:25,551
God only smiles on us when we're in a pinch.

330
00:18:25,934 --> 00:18:29,849
That's why I mortgaged this condo and borrowed money.

331
00:18:30,192 --> 00:18:31,500
Huh?

332
00:18:31,684 --> 00:18:34,894
After that, we had a huge fight.

333
00:18:34,910 --> 00:18:39,027
When the ashtray Chiyoko threw hit my eye, I felt a shock run through me.

334
00:18:39,486 --> 00:18:43,782
Now, with things as they are,
the murder plan I thought of

335
00:18:43,862 --> 00:18:48,462
when I found that suicide note before... I can carry it out.

336
00:18:48,578 --> 00:18:51,247
I felt that God was on my side.

337
00:18:55,562 --> 00:18:58,462
Hey, how did you know who the culprit was?

338
00:18:58,546 --> 00:19:00,590
I suspected it from the note,

339
00:19:00,673 --> 00:19:02,762
but I became certain when I heard the father and son talking

340
00:19:02,762 --> 00:19:05,462
at the front door.

341
00:19:05,553 --> 00:19:08,848
"With that pudding-head of yours, there's no way you'll pass."

342
00:19:08,932 --> 00:19:13,478
The only way he could know what was under the hat of his son,

343
00:19:13,561 --> 00:19:18,024
who he hadn't seen in over a year,

344
00:19:18,108 --> 00:19:22,153
was if he saw his son ringing the doorbell
through the peephole while his wife was hanging.

345
00:19:22,237 --> 00:19:26,324
But if the son was wearing his hat, he wouldn't have seen.

346
00:19:26,658 --> 00:19:27,659
Hmph.

347
00:19:28,243 --> 00:19:32,664
The son has a hobby of peeking back through the peephole.

348
00:19:33,123 --> 00:19:34,165
Huh?

349
00:19:34,666 --> 00:19:35,667
Hmph.

350
00:19:36,251 --> 00:19:40,505
If you're wearing a cap with a brim,
you can't look through unless you take it off, right?

351
00:19:43,591 --> 00:19:49,597
♪~♪

352
00:20:57,373 --> 00:21:03,171
♪~♪

353
00:21:04,923 --> 00:21:08,134
Still, he was quite a sharp guy, wasn't he?

354
00:21:08,218 --> 00:21:10,553
He's Yumi-san's ex-boyfriend, right?

355
00:21:10,637 --> 00:21:12,555
From what I heard before,

356
00:21:12,639 --> 00:21:15,683
I imagined someone more host-like.

357
00:21:15,975 --> 00:21:18,520
Well, it's fine. He's sharp,

358
00:21:18,603 --> 00:21:21,814
and he seemed to help solve the case.

359
00:21:21,898 --> 00:21:26,486
Yeah, I got a bit excited too, solving a case with a celebrity.

360
00:21:26,569 --> 00:21:28,363
Celebrity? Huh?

361
00:21:28,446 --> 00:21:31,491
Was there an actor named Shukichi Haneda?

362
00:21:31,574 --> 00:21:32,951
Look, this guy.

363
00:21:33,034 --> 00:21:35,495
Congratulations on winning the Meijin title and four crowns.

364
00:21:35,578 --> 00:21:36,829
Ah!

365
00:21:36,913 --> 00:21:38,831
It's the Meijin, Taiko!

366
00:21:38,915 --> 00:21:40,875
Ayumi's mom is a big fan too.

367
00:21:40,959 --> 00:21:43,920
But what does the Meijin have to do with him?

368
00:21:44,003 --> 00:21:45,547
Look closely.

369
00:21:45,630 --> 00:21:47,507
Hmm? Hmm...

370
00:21:47,590 --> 00:21:51,010
"I guess the sideways rook worked out well today..."

371
00:21:51,094 --> 00:21:54,013
Hmm...

372
00:21:57,100 --> 00:21:58,351
Ah!

373
00:21:58,434 --> 00:21:59,477
That cowlick!

374
00:21:59,561 --> 00:22:01,980
That's that guy!

375
00:22:02,522 --> 00:22:04,649
I see.

376
00:22:04,732 --> 00:22:08,319
The kanji in his name resembles that of Hideyoshi Hashiba,

377
00:22:08,403 --> 00:22:12,865
so that's why he's called Taiko.

378
00:22:12,949 --> 00:22:15,493
Ah, actually, he went to the shogi hall for a qualifying match that day,

379
00:22:15,577 --> 00:22:16,869
but he didn't want Yumi to find out

380
00:22:16,953 --> 00:22:18,062
that he's a shogi player yet.

381
00:22:18,146 --> 00:22:20,081
Why not? Being a Meijin is awesome!

382
00:22:20,164 --> 00:22:23,376
So then, what were the seven things he was collecting?

383
00:22:23,918 --> 00:22:27,046
Well, when it comes to seven in shogi...

384
00:22:28,089 --> 00:22:29,632
Huh?

385
00:22:32,760 --> 00:22:33,886
(Flashback) Haah, haah...

386
00:22:34,387 --> 00:22:36,889
Yumi-tan, I did it!

387
00:22:37,098 --> 00:22:39,892
I finally got the Meijin title I've been longing for!

388
00:22:40,101 --> 00:22:41,477
Yumi-tan!

389
00:22:41,561 --> 00:22:44,397
Ah... you're late, Chuukichi.

390
00:22:44,981 --> 00:22:48,026
Ah, sorry, sorry. The match ran longer than I expected.

391
00:22:48,109 --> 00:22:50,278
Huh? Were you playing a game?

392
00:22:50,361 --> 00:22:54,157
Ah... well, you could call it a game, but...

393
00:22:54,240 --> 00:22:55,283
Actually, today I...

394
00:22:55,366 --> 00:22:57,201
More importantly, look at this news.

395
00:22:57,285 --> 00:22:58,286
Ah... news?

396
00:22:58,953 --> 00:23:02,123
Yokozuna Tenho won the summer tournament,

397
00:23:02,206 --> 00:23:04,792
winning all six tournaments in a row.

398
00:23:05,168 --> 00:23:09,297
That's amazing. Winning for an entire year straight.

399
00:23:09,881 --> 00:23:13,009
If a prince-like man like that were my husband,

400
00:23:13,092 --> 00:23:16,054
I'd feel like a queen.

401
00:23:16,888 --> 00:23:18,848
Heh heh. Don't worry.

402
00:23:18,931 --> 00:23:22,101
I don't expect anything like that from you, Chuukichi.

403
00:23:22,435 --> 00:23:26,981
Kioh, Osho, Oza, Kisei,

404
00:23:27,065 --> 00:23:31,110
Oi, Ryuoh, Meijin.

405
00:23:32,070 --> 00:23:34,614
Seven crowns!

406
00:23:35,448 --> 00:23:38,951
Huh? Chuukichi is a Meijin?

407
00:23:39,035 --> 00:23:42,330
Y-yes, that's right. Actually...

408
00:23:42,413 --> 00:23:46,167
It's probably fishing champion or a game champion or something.

409
00:23:46,250 --> 00:23:47,710
That sounds like him.

410
00:23:47,794 --> 00:23:49,629
Ah, um...

411
00:23:51,464 --> 00:23:57,470
(Bell tolls)

412
00:23:58,596 --> 00:24:00,723
The groom has collapsed!

413
00:24:02,767 --> 00:24:04,143
Ah...

414
00:24:05,228 --> 00:24:11,401
So these two murder cases appear to be the work of the same culprit.

415
00:24:11,776 --> 00:24:15,446
I see. If we use that...

416
00:24:15,862 --> 00:24:17,162
Next Conan,

417
00:24:17,162 --> 00:24:21,162
"The Wedding Reception and Two Gunshots."

418
00:24:36,762 --> 00:24:38,862
Next Conan's Hint:

419
00:24:38,862 --> 00:24:40,562
"Bamboo Forest."
